+### `REVIEW_ERROR phase=fix reason=fix_failed message="claude stop hook did not signal completion"`
+
+Cause: a tmux review-fix pass finished cleanly but Claude Code's Stop hook never wrote the `.done` sentinel (a known tmux stop-hook signaling issue). Newer builds ship a tolerant fallback that accepts a clean-exit fix with a diff to commit. Tasks parked on the old failure may already hold completed, committed work. Fix: follow the evidence-check-then-clear recovery in [notes/claude-tmux-launch-mode.md](notes/claude-tmux-launch-mode.md#recovery-for-tasks-stuck-on-the-old-failure) — never clear the marker without first confirming the fix commit/artifacts exist. Recommended workaround for affected Claude Code versions: `claude.mode: headless`.
+
 ### `reviewer_tampered`, `triage_tampered`, or `fix_tampered`
 
 Cause: an agent changed a protected file such as `plan.md`, `worktree.yml`, or `task.md` during a phase that must not touch it. Fix: inspect the worktree, restore the protected file from git if needed, clear the error marker, and re-run.
