+      # Tolerant-completion predicate for the review-fix exit_code_only
+      # spawn. A tmux fix pass can finish cleanly — the fix agent returns to
+      # its idle prompt with a diff staged in the worktree — yet the Stop
+      # hook never lands the `.done` sentinel (fires late, or the pane is
+      # torn down before scripts/stop_hook.sh completes; see
+      # docs/notes/claude-tmux-stop-hook-signaling.md). Without this the
+      # launcher drains to `{status: :timeout, "claude stop hook did not
+      # signal completion"}`, `agent_failed?` reads it as failure, and the
+      # completed work is stranded behind a `REVIEW_ERROR phase=fix
+      # reason=fix_failed` marker (observed on tasks 58/#622, 287/#623,
+      # 288/#624).
+      #
+      # This predicate is consulted ONLY at the sentinel-missing deadline
+      # and ONLY after the launcher has confirmed a clean exit (pane
+      # readable, session present — a crashed/unreadable pane never reaches
+      # here). It proves the fix pass genuinely ran by requiring:
+      #   - the worktree is readable, and
+      #   - this pass's triage escalations exist (a real fix input), and
+      #   - the fix agent left changes to commit (dirty worktree).
+      # On accept it returns the audit-event payload and the launcher
+      # returns `{status: :ok, fallback: true}`. The normal post-fix flow
+      # then runs unchanged — auto-commit creates the commit, the guardrail
+      # runs, and write_fix_success drops the sentinel — so the
+      # "commit-since-pass-start" guarantee (R3) is enforced downstream, not
+      # laundered here. A pass with no diff to commit stays strict (falls to
+      # REVIEW_ERROR / the daemon stop-hook healer) because at fix time the
+      # accepted findings should always produce edits; zero-finding passes
+      # short-circuit before Phase 4 and never reach this predicate.
+      def fix_completion_fallback(task, ctx, session_name)
+        pass = ctx.pass
+        worktree_path = ctx.worktree_path
+        task_folder = ctx.task_folder
+        lambda do |_evidence, _task|
+          next nil unless File.directory?(worktree_path.to_s)
+
+          escalations = File.join(task_folder, "reviews", "escalations-#{format('%02d', pass)}.md")
+          next nil unless File.exist?(escalations)
+
+          next nil unless worktree_status(worktree_path) == :dirty
+
+          {
+            phase: "fix",
+            pass: pass,
+            stage: "6-review", # coding-scoped: coding review stage event
+            agent: "fix-pass-#{format('%02d', pass)}",
+            session: session_name,
+            artifacts: "reviews/escalations-#{format('%02d', pass)}.md",
+            evidence: "worktree_changes_pending_commit",
+            log_label: "review-fix-pass#{format('%02d', pass)}"
+          }
+        end
+      end
+
       # The triage bias configured for this run, surfaced into commit
       # trailers so `hive metrics rollback-rate` can compare bias presets.
       # Defaults to "courageous" — same default as Triage.run! itself.
