+**Action:** Added a tolerant completion fallback for the tmux
+`:exit_code_only` path so a clean-exit Claude review-fix pass with a diff to
+commit is accepted even when the Stop hook never writes the `.done` sentinel.
+`ClaudeLauncher.wait_for_done_signal` now takes an opt-in
+`completion_fallback` predicate; on a confirmed clean exit it returns
+`{status: :ok, fallback: true}` and emits a non-error
+`claude_completion_fallback` event instead of the strict
+"claude stop hook did not signal completion" timeout. Review-fix supplies the
+predicate (readable worktree + this pass's escalations + dirty worktree); the
+normal post-fix auto-commit/guardrail/write_fix_success flow runs unchanged, so
+genuine failures still stamp REVIEW_ERROR. Documented the root-cause analysis,
+the mode policy (headless stays the recommended workaround), and the guarded
+manual recovery for tasks stuck on the pre-fallback failure.
+
+**Refs:** [[stages/review]] · [[modules/events]]
