+## Tmux stop-hook tolerant completion (Phase 4 fix)
+
+In tmux mode the Phase 4 fix agent runs through the launcher's
+`:exit_code_only` completion path, whose only completion signal is the Stop
+hook's `.done` sentinel. A clean fix run can finish — leaving a diff staged in
+the worktree — yet the Stop hook never writes `.done` (a Claude Code tmux
+signaling issue; see `docs/notes/claude-tmux-stop-hook-signaling.md`). Without
+mitigation `wait_for_done_signal` drains to
+`{status: :timeout, "claude stop hook did not signal completion"}`,
+`agent_failed?` reads it as failure, and the pass strands completed work behind
+`REVIEW_ERROR phase=fix reason=fix_failed`.
+
+`spawn_fix_agent` now passes a `completion_fallback` predicate
+(`fix_completion_fallback`) into `Base.spawn_claude!`. At the sentinel-missing
+deadline the launcher, **only** on a confirmed clean exit (pane readable,
+session present), consults the predicate; it returns truthy when the worktree is
+readable, this pass's `escalations-NN.md` exists, and the worktree is dirty (a
+fix diff pending commit). On accept the launcher returns
+`{status: :ok, fallback: true}` and emits a non-error `claude_completion_fallback`
+event ([[modules/events]]); the normal post-fix flow (auto-commit → guardrail →
+`write_fix_success`) then runs unchanged. Crashes, unreadable panes, non-zero
+exits, and passes with no diff stay strict and still stamp `REVIEW_ERROR`.
+
+Recovery for tasks parked on the pre-fallback failure and the mode policy
+(headless stays the recommended workaround for affected Claude Code versions)
+are documented in `docs/notes/claude-tmux-launch-mode.md`.
+
 ## Tests
 
 - `test/integration/run_review_test.rb` — pre-flight short-circuits, missing-worktree handling, clean fast path, CI hard-block, wall-clock cap including triage-retry handoff to `REVIEW_STALE`, reviewers all-limit markers, triage/CI/fix limit vs non-limit failure classification, transient triage retry, ad-hoc fix-off/fix-opt-in branching, and `message=` surfacing on terminal phase-agent errors.
